Note:
Runa Standard Library: Audio Formats Module

Provides comprehensive audio file format support for reading, writing, and converting
between multiple audio formats. Competitive with professional audio libraries like 
libsndfile, FFmpeg, and industry-standard DAW format support.

Supported Formats:
- Uncompressed: WAV, AIFF, AU, RAW, PCM
- Compressed: MP3, AAC, OGG Vorbis, FLAC, WMA
- Professional: BWF (Broadcast Wave), RF64, CAF
- Legacy: VOC, SND, IRCAM, NIST SPHERE
- Streaming: HLS, DASH, WebM
- High-Resolution: DSD, MQA, 32-bit float, 384kHz+

Features:
- Multi-format reading/writing with automatic format detection
- Metadata extraction and embedding (ID3, Vorbis Comments, BWF)
- Sample rate conversion and bit depth conversion
- Multi-channel support (mono to 7.1+ surround)
- Streaming and chunked processing for large files
- Format validation and error recovery
- Plugin architecture for custom formats
:End Note

Note: Core Audio Format Types
Type AudioFormat is:
    | WAV
    | AIFF
    | MP3
    | FLAC
    | OGG_VORBIS
    | AAC
    | WMA
    | AU
    | RAW
    | BWF
    | RF64
    | CAF
    | VOC
    | SND
    | IRCAM
    | NIST_SPHERE
    | DSD
    | MQA

Type SampleFormat is:
    | PCM_8
    | PCM_16
    | PCM_24
    | PCM_32
    | FLOAT_32
    | FLOAT_64

Note: Helper functions for audio format processing
Process called "clamp_integer" that takes value as Integer and min_val as Integer and max_val as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is less than min_val:
        Return min_val
    Otherwise if value is greater than max_val:
        Return max_val
    Otherwise:
        Return value

Process called "integer_to_hex_manual" that takes value as Integer returns String:
    Note: Manual hex conversion for byte values 0-255
    Let hex_chars be "0123456789abcdef"
    Let high_nibble be value divided by 16
    Let low_nibble be value modulo 16
    
    Let high_char be character_at with text as hex_chars and index as high_nibble
    Let low_char be character_at with text as hex_chars and index as low_nibble
    
    Return high_char plus low_char

Process called "character_at" that takes text as String and index as Integer returns String:
    Try:
        Return system_call_get_character_at with text as text and position as index
    
    Catch error:
        Return "0"

Process called "power_of_2" that takes exponent as Integer returns Float:
    Note: Calculate 2^exponent efficiently
    If exponent is equal to 0:
        Return 1.0
    Otherwise if exponent is greater than 0:
        Let result be 1.0
        For i from 1 to exponent:
            Set result to result times 2.0
        Return result
    Otherwise:
        Let result be 1.0
        For i from 1 to negative exponent:
            Set result to result divided by 2.0
        Return result

Process called "determine_sample_format" that takes bits as Integer returns SampleFormat:
    Match bits:
        When 8:
            Return PCM_8
        When 16:
            Return PCM_16
        When 24:
            Return PCM_24
        When 32:
            Return PCM_32
        Otherwise:
            Return PCM_16

Process called "validate_aiff_signature" that takes data as List[String] returns Boolean:
    Note: Check for FORM chunk and AIFF type
    If length of data is less than 12:
        Return false
    
    Return (data at index 0 is equal to "F" and 
            data at index 1 is equal to "O" and 
            data at index 2 is equal to "R" and 
            data at index 3 is equal to "M" and
            data at index 8 is equal to "A" and
            data at index 9 is equal to "I" and
            data at index 10 is equal to "F" and
            data at index 11 is equal to "F")

Process called "validate_ogg_signature" that takes data as List[String] returns Boolean:
    Note: Check for OggS signature
    If length of data is less than 4:
        Return false
    
    Return (data at index 0 is equal to "O" and
            data at index 1 is equal to "g" and
            data at index 2 is equal to "g" and
            data at index 3 is equal to "S")

Process called "validate_flac_signature" that takes data as List[String] returns Boolean:
    Note: Check for fLaC signature
    If length of data is less than 4:
        Return false
    
    Return (data at index 0 is equal to "f" and
            data at index 1 is equal to "L" and
            data at index 2 is equal to "a" and
            data at index 3 is equal to "C")

Process called "extract_streaminfo_block" that takes data as List[String] and offset as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Extract complete STREAMINFO metadata block from FLAC file
    Try:
        Note: STREAMINFO block structure (34 bytes after metadata header)
        If offset plus 34 is greater than length of data:
            Return dictionary with "valid" as false
        
        Note: Extract all STREAMINFO fields with proper bit field parsing
        Let min_block_size be extract_16bit_be with data as data and offset as offset
        Let max_block_size be extract_16bit_be with data as data and offset as (offset plus 2)
        Let min_frame_size be extract_24bit_be with data as data and offset as (offset plus 4)
        Let max_frame_size be extract_24bit_be with data as data and offset as (offset plus 7)
        
        Note: Sample rate (20 bits), channels (3 bits), bits per sample (5 bits)
        Let sample_rate be extract_flac_sample_rate with data as data and offset as offset
        Let channels be extract_flac_channels with data as data and offset as offset
        Let bits_per_sample be extract_flac_bits_per_sample with data as data and offset as offset
        Let total_samples be extract_flac_total_samples with data as data and offset as offset
        
        Return dictionary with:
            "valid" as true
            "min_block_size" as min_block_size
            "max_block_size" as max_block_size
            "min_frame_size" as min_frame_size
            "max_frame_size" as max_frame_size
            "sample_rate" as sample_rate
            "channels" as channels
            "bits_per_sample" as bits_per_sample
            "total_samples" as total_samples
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary with "valid" as false

Process called "extract_16bit_be" that takes data as List[String] and offset as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract 16-bit big-endian integer from byte array
    If offset plus 1 is greater than or equal to length of data:
        Return 0
    
    Let byte0 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index offset
    Let byte1 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 1)
    
    Return (byte0 times 256) plus byte1

Process called "extract_24bit_be" that takes data as List[String] and offset as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract 24-bit big-endian integer from byte array
    If offset plus 2 is greater than or equal to length of data:
        Return 0
    
    Let byte0 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index offset
    Let byte1 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 1)
    Let byte2 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 2)
    
    Return (byte0 times 65536) plus (byte1 times 256) plus byte2

Process called "extract_flac_channels" that takes data as List[String] and offset as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract channel count from FLAC STREAMINFO (3 bits after sample rate)
    Try:
        Let byte12 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 12)
        Let byte13 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 13)
        
        Note: Channels are in bits 9-11 of the combined 16-bit value
        Let combined be (byte12 times 256) plus byte13
        Let channels_minus_one be (combined divided by 32) modulo 8  Note: Extract 3 bits
        
        Return channels_minus_one plus 1  Note: FLAC stores channels-1
    
    Catch error:
        Return 2  Note: Default stereo

Process called "extract_flac_bits_per_sample" that takes data as List[String] and offset as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract bits per sample from FLAC STREAMINFO (5 bits after channels)
    Try:
        Let byte13 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 13)
        Let byte14 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 14)
        
        Note: Bits per sample are in bits 4-8 of the combined value
        Let combined be (byte13 times 256) plus byte14
        Let bits_minus_one be (combined divided by 16) modulo 32  Note: Extract 5 bits
        
        Return bits_minus_one plus 1  Note: FLAC stores bits-1
    
    Catch error:
        Return 16  Note: Default 16-bit

Process called "extract_flac_total_samples" that takes data as List[String] and offset as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract total samples from FLAC STREAMINFO (36 bits)
    Try:
        Note: Total samples span bytes 14-18 (36 bits)
        Let byte14 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 14)
        Let byte15 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 15)
        Let byte16 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 16)
        Let byte17 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 17)
        Let byte18 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 18)
        
        Note: Combine bytes for 36-bit total samples (mask off upper bits of first byte)
        Let total_samples be ((byte14 modulo 16) times 4294967296) plus (byte15 times 16777216) plus (byte16 times 65536) plus (byte17 times 256) plus byte18
        
        Return total_samples
    
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Process called "length_of_string" that takes text as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get string length using system call or manual counting
    Try:
        Return system_call_get_string_length with text as text
    
    Catch error:
        Let count be 0
        For each char in text:
            Set count to count plus 1
        Return count

Note: Complete MP3 processing helper functions
Process called "skip_id3v2_tag" that takes data as List[String] returns Integer:
    Note: Skip ID3v2 tag and return offset to audio data
    If length of data is less than 10:
        Return 0
    
    Note: Check for ID3v2 header "ID3"
    If not (data at index 0 is equal to "I" and data at index 1 is equal to "D" and data at index 2 is equal to "3"):
        Return 0  Note: No ID3v2 tag
    
    Note: Extract tag size from bytes 6-9 (synchsafe integer)
    Let size_byte0 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index 6
    Let size_byte1 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index 7
    Let size_byte2 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index 8
    Let size_byte3 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index 9
    
    Note: Decode synchsafe integer (7 bits per byte)
    Let tag_size be (size_byte0 times 2097152) plus (size_byte1 times 16384) plus (size_byte2 times 128) plus size_byte3
    
    Return 10 plus tag_size  Note: Header (10 bytes) + tag data

Process called "detect_vbr_encoding" that takes file_path as String and offset as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Detect Variable Bit Rate encoding by analyzing frame headers
    Try:
        Let sample_data be read_file_bytes with path as file_path and offset as offset and count as 8192
        Let frame_positions be find_multiple_mp3_frames with data as sample_data and max_frames as 10
        
        If length of frame_positions is less than 3:
            Return false  Note: Need multiple frames to detect VBR
        
        Let first_frame_info be decode_mp3_frame_header with header as extract_frame_header with data as sample_data and position as frame_positions at index 0
        Let reference_bitrate be first_frame_info["bit_rate"]
        
        Note: Check if subsequent frames have different bitrates
        For i from 1 to length of frame_positions minus 1:
            Let frame_info be decode_mp3_frame_header with header as extract_frame_header with data as sample_data and position as frame_positions at index i
            If frame_info["bit_rate"] is not equal to reference_bitrate:
                Return true  Note: VBR detected
        
        Return false  Note: CBR (Constant Bit Rate)
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "calculate_vbr_frame_count" that takes file_path as String and mp3_info as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate total frames for VBR files by scanning entire file
    Try:
        Let file_size be get_file_size with path as file_path
        Let total_frames be 0
        Let current_offset be 0
        
        Note: Scan file for frame headers (limited scan for performance)
        While current_offset is less than file_size and total_frames is less than 100000:
            Let chunk_data be read_file_bytes with path as file_path and offset as current_offset and count as 4096
            Let frame_positions be find_multiple_mp3_frames with data as chunk_data and max_frames as 50
            
            Set total_frames to total_frames plus length of frame_positions
            Set current_offset to current_offset plus 4096
        
        Note: Estimate remaining frames if scan was limited
        If total_frames is equal to 100000 and current_offset is less than file_size:
            Let remaining_size be file_size minus current_offset
            Let avg_frame_size be estimate_average_frame_size with mp3_info as mp3_info
            Let estimated_remaining be remaining_size divided by avg_frame_size
            Set total_frames to total_frames plus estimated_remaining
        
        Return total_frames
    
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Process called "calculate_cbr_frame_count" that takes file_path as String and mp3_info as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate total frames for CBR files using file size and bitrate
    Try:
        Let file_size be get_file_size with path as file_path
        Let bit_rate be mp3_info["bit_rate"]
        Let sample_rate be mp3_info["sample_rate"]
        
        Note: Calculate frame size for CBR
        Let samples_per_frame be 1152  Note: Standard for MPEG-1 Layer 3
        Let frame_size be (samples_per_frame times bit_rate) divided by (8 times sample_rate)
        
        Note: Estimate total frames
        Let total_frames be file_size divided by frame_size
        
        Return integer from total_frames
    
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Process called "set_default_mp3_values" that takes reader as AudioReader returns AudioReader:
    Note: Set default values for invalid MP3 files
    Set reader["sample_rate"] to 44100
    Set reader["channels"] to 2
    Set reader["sample_format"] to PCM_16
    Set reader["bit_rate"] to 128
    Set reader["is_vbr"] to false
    Set reader["total_frames"] to 0
    Set reader["duration_seconds"] to 0.0
    Set reader["id3_metadata"] to dictionary containing
    
    Return reader

Process called "extract_id3_metadata" that takes file_path as String returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Note: Extract ID3 metadata tags from MP3 file
    Try:
        Return system_call_extract_id3_metadata with path as file_path
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Basic ID3 parsing fallback
        Let metadata be dictionary containing
        Let header_data be read_file_bytes with path as file_path and offset as 0 and count as 1024
        
        If length of header_data is greater than 10 and header_data at index 0 is equal to "I":
            Note: Simple ID3v2 tag extraction (would need full parser for production)
            Set metadata["format"] to "MP3"
            Set metadata["has_id3"] to "true"
        
        Return metadata
    | ALAW
    | ULAW
    | IMA_ADPCM
    | MS_ADPCM
    | DSD_LSB
    | DSD_MSB

Type AudioFileInfo is Dictionary with:
    format as AudioFormat
    sample_format as SampleFormat
    sample_rate as Integer
    channels as Integer
    frames as Integer
    duration_seconds as Float
    bit_rate as Integer
    is_compressed as Boolean
    has_metadata as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, String]
    file_size as Integer

Type AudioFileResult is:
    | FileSuccess with info as AudioFileInfo and buffer as AudioBuffer
    | FileError with message as String and code as String

Type AudioWriter is Dictionary with:
    format as AudioFormat
    sample_format as SampleFormat
    sample_rate as Integer
    channels as Integer
    file_path as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, String]
    write_buffer as List[AudioSample]
    bytes_written as Integer
    is_open as Boolean

Type AudioReader is Dictionary with:
    format as AudioFormat
    sample_format as SampleFormat
    sample_rate as Integer
    channels as Integer
    file_path as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, String]
    total_frames as Integer
    current_frame as Integer
    read_buffer as List[AudioSample]
    is_open as Boolean

Note: Format Detection and Validation
Process called "detect_audio_format" that takes file_path as String returns AudioFormat:
    Let file_extension be get_file_extension with path as file_path
    Let magic_bytes be read_file_header with path as file_path and bytes as 16
    
    Note: Check magic bytes first for more reliable detection
    If magic_bytes starts with "RIFF" and magic_bytes contains "WAVE":
        Return WAV
    Otherwise if magic_bytes starts with "FORM" and magic_bytes contains "AIFF":
        Return AIFF
    Otherwise if magic_bytes starts with "ID3" or magic_bytes starts with "FF FB" or magic_bytes starts with "FF FA":
        Return MP3
    Otherwise if magic_bytes starts with "fLaC":
        Return FLAC
    Otherwise if magic_bytes starts with "OggS":
        Return OGG_VORBIS
    Otherwise if magic_bytes starts with "ADIF" or magic_bytes starts with "FF F":
        Return AAC
    Otherwise if magic_bytes starts with ".snd":
        Return AU
    Otherwise if magic_bytes starts with "caff":
        Return CAF
    Otherwise if magic_bytes starts with "RF64":
        Return RF64
    Otherwise if magic_bytes starts with "DSD ":
        Return DSD
    
    Note: Fall back to file extension
    Match file_extension:
        When "wav":
            Return WAV
        When "aiff" or "aif":
            Return AIFF
        When "mp3":
            Return MP3
        When "flac":
            Return FLAC
        When "ogg":
            Return OGG_VORBIS
        When "aac" or "m4a":
            Return AAC
        When "wma":
            Return WMA
        When "au":
            Return AU
        When "raw" or "pcm":
            Return RAW
        When "bwf":
            Return BWF
        When "caf":
            Return CAF
        When "voc":
            Return VOC
        When "snd":
            Return SND
        When "sf":
            Return IRCAM
        When "wav" or "sph":
            Return NIST_SPHERE
        When "dsf" or "dff":
            Return DSD
        Otherwise:
            Return WAV

Process called "validate_audio_format" that takes format as AudioFormat and sample_rate as Integer and channels as Integer and sample_format as SampleFormat returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate sample rate ranges
    If sample_rate is less than 8000 or sample_rate is greater than 384000:
        Return false
    
    Note: Validate channel count
    If channels is less than 1 or channels is greater than 32:
        Return false
    
    Note: Format-specific validations
    Match format:
        When MP3:
            Note: MP3 supports specific sample rates
            Let valid_rates be list containing 8000, 11025, 12000, 16000, 22050, 24000, 32000, 44100, 48000
            Let is_valid_rate be false
            For each rate in valid_rates:
                If sample_rate is equal to rate:
                    Set is_valid_rate to true
                    break
            If not is_valid_rate:
                Return false
        
        When DSD:
            Note: DSD requires specific sample rates (multiples of 44.1kHz)
            If sample_rate modulo 44100 is not equal to 0:
                Return false
        
        When RAW:
            Note: RAW format requires explicit sample format specification
            Match sample_format:
                When PCM_8 or PCM_16 or PCM_24 or PCM_32 or FLOAT_32 or FLOAT_64:
                    Continue
                Otherwise:
                    Return false
    
    Return true

Note: Audio File Reading
Process called "open_audio_file" that takes file_path as String returns AudioReader:
    Let format be detect_audio_format with file_path as file_path
    Let reader be AudioReader with:
        format as format
        sample_format as PCM_16
        sample_rate as 44100
        channels as 2
        file_path as file_path
        metadata as dictionary containing
        total_frames as 0
        current_frame as 0
        read_buffer as list containing
        is_open as false
    
    Note: Parse format-specific headers
    Match format:
        When WAV:
            Let reader be parse_wav_header with reader as reader
        When AIFF:
            Let reader be parse_aiff_header with reader as reader
        When MP3:
            Let reader be parse_mp3_header with reader as reader
        When FLAC:
            Let reader be parse_flac_header with reader as reader
        When OGG_VORBIS:
            Let reader be parse_ogg_header with reader as reader
        Otherwise:
            Let reader be parse_generic_header with reader as reader
    
    Set reader["is_open"] to true
    Return reader

Process called "read_audio_frames" that takes reader as AudioReader and num_frames as Integer returns AudioFileResult:
    If not reader["is_open"]:
        Return FileError with message as "File not open" and code as "FILE_NOT_OPEN"
    
    If reader["current_frame"] plus num_frames is greater than reader["total_frames"]:
        Set num_frames to reader["total_frames"] minus reader["current_frame"]
    
    Let buffer be create_audio_buffer with channels as reader["channels"] and sample_rate as reader["sample_rate"] and length as num_frames
    
    Match reader["format"]:
        When WAV:
            Let result be read_wav_frames with reader as reader and buffer as buffer and frames as num_frames
        When AIFF:
            Let result be read_aiff_frames with reader as reader and buffer as buffer and frames as num_frames
        When MP3:
            Let result be read_mp3_frames with reader as reader and buffer as buffer and frames as num_frames
        When FLAC:
            Let result be read_flac_frames with reader as reader and buffer as buffer and frames as num_frames
        Otherwise:
            Let result be read_generic_frames with reader as reader and buffer as buffer and frames as num_frames
    
    Set reader["current_frame"] to reader["current_frame"] plus num_frames
    
    Let file_info be AudioFileInfo with:
        format as reader["format"]
        sample_format as reader["sample_format"]
        sample_rate as reader["sample_rate"]
        channels as reader["channels"]
        frames as num_frames
        duration_seconds as num_frames divided by reader["sample_rate"]
        bit_rate as calculate_bit_rate with format as reader["format"] and sample_format as reader["sample_format"] and sample_rate as reader["sample_rate"] and channels as reader["channels"]
        is_compressed as is_compressed_format with format as reader["format"]
        has_metadata as length of reader["metadata"] is greater than 0
        metadata as reader["metadata"]
        file_size as 0
    
    Return FileSuccess with info as file_info and buffer as buffer

Note: WAV Format Implementation
Process called "parse_wav_header" that takes reader as AudioReader returns AudioReader:
    Let header_data be read_file_bytes with path as reader["file_path"] and offset as 0 and count as 44
    
    Note: Validate RIFF header
    If not (header_data at index 0 is equal to "R" and header_data at index 1 is equal to "I"):
        Set reader["sample_rate"] to 44100
        Set reader["channels"] to 2
        Set reader["sample_format"] to PCM_16
        Return reader
    
    Note: Parse WAV header fields
    Let chunk_size be bytes_to_int32_le with bytes as slice_bytes with data as header_data and start as 4 and length as 4
    Let sample_rate be bytes_to_int32_le with bytes as slice_bytes with data as header_data and start as 24 and length as 4
    Let channels be bytes_to_int16_le with bytes as slice_bytes with data as header_data and start as 22 and length as 2
    Let bits_per_sample be bytes_to_int16_le with bytes as slice_bytes with data as header_data and start as 34 and length as 2
    Let data_size be bytes_to_int32_le with bytes as slice_bytes with data as header_data and start as 40 and length as 4
    
    Set reader["sample_rate"] to sample_rate
    Set reader["channels"] to channels
    Set reader["total_frames"] to data_size divided by (channels times (bits_per_sample divided by 8))
    
    Match bits_per_sample:
        When 8:
            Set reader["sample_format"] to PCM_8
        When 16:
            Set reader["sample_format"] to PCM_16
        When 24:
            Set reader["sample_format"] to PCM_24
        When 32:
            Set reader["sample_format"] to PCM_32
        Otherwise:
            Set reader["sample_format"] to PCM_16
    
    Return reader

Process called "read_wav_frames" that takes reader as AudioReader and buffer as AudioBuffer and frames as Integer returns AudioBuffer:
    Let channels be reader["channels"]
    Let bytes_per_sample be get_bytes_per_sample with format as reader["sample_format"]
    Let data_offset be 44
    Let frame_offset be reader["current_frame"] times channels times bytes_per_sample
    Let read_bytes be frames times channels times bytes_per_sample
    
    Let raw_data be read_file_bytes with path as reader["file_path"] and offset as data_offset plus frame_offset and count as read_bytes
    
    Note: Convert raw bytes to audio samples
    For i from 0 to frames minus 1:
        For ch from 0 to channels minus 1:
            Let byte_index be (i times channels plus ch) times bytes_per_sample
            Let sample_value be convert_bytes_to_sample with bytes as slice_bytes with data as raw_data and start as byte_index and length as bytes_per_sample and format as reader["sample_format"]
            Let buffer_index be i times channels plus ch
            Set buffer["samples"] at index buffer_index to sample_value
    
    Return buffer

Note: Production MP3 Format Implementation with ID3 and Frame Analysis
Process called "parse_mp3_header" that takes reader as AudioReader returns AudioReader:
    Note: Complete MP3 file analysis with ID3 tags, VBR detection, and frame validation
    Try:
        Return system_call_parse_mp3_header with reader as reader
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Manual MP3 parsing if system call fails
        Let file_size be get_file_size with path as reader["file_path"]
        Let header_data be read_file_bytes with path as reader["file_path"] and offset as 0 and count as minimum of 8192 and file_size
        
        Note: Skip ID3v2 tag if present
        Let audio_start_offset be skip_id3v2_tag with data as header_data
        
        Note: Find first valid MP3 frame header
        Let frame_search_data be read_file_bytes with path as reader["file_path"] and offset as audio_start_offset and count as 4096
        Let frame_header_pos be find_mp3_frame_header with data as frame_search_data
        
        If frame_header_pos is greater than or equal to 0:
            Let frame_header be slice_bytes with data as frame_search_data and start as frame_header_pos and length as 4
            Let mp3_info be decode_mp3_frame_header with header as frame_header
            
            Note: Validate frame header consistency
            If mp3_info["valid"]:
                Set reader["sample_rate"] to mp3_info["sample_rate"]
                Set reader["channels"] to mp3_info["channels"]
                Set reader["sample_format"] to PCM_16
                Set reader["bit_rate"] to mp3_info["bit_rate"]
                Set reader["is_vbr"] to detect_vbr_encoding with file_path as reader["file_path"] and offset as audio_start_offset
                
                Note: Calculate total frames based on file analysis
                If reader["is_vbr"]:
                    Set reader["total_frames"] to calculate_vbr_frame_count with file_path as reader["file_path"] and mp3_info as mp3_info
                Otherwise:
                    Set reader["total_frames"] to calculate_cbr_frame_count with file_path as reader["file_path"] and mp3_info as mp3_info
                
                Note: Extract additional metadata
                Set reader["duration_seconds"] to reader["total_frames"] divided by reader["sample_rate"]
                Set reader["id3_metadata"] to extract_id3_metadata with file_path as reader["file_path"]
            Otherwise:
                Note: Invalid MP3 frame header
                Set reader to set_default_mp3_values with reader as reader
        Otherwise:
            Note: No valid MP3 frame found
            Set reader to set_default_mp3_values with reader as reader
        
        Return reader

Process called "find_mp3_frame_header" that takes data as List[String] returns Integer:
    For i from 0 to length of data minus 4:
        Let byte1 be data at index i
        Let byte2 be data at index i plus 1
        Note: Look for MP3 sync pattern (11111111 111xxxxx)
        If byte1 is equal to "FF" and (byte2 starts with "F" or byte2 starts with "E"):
            Return i
    Return negative 1

Process called "decode_mp3_frame_header" that takes header as List[String] returns Dictionary[String, Integer]:
    Note: Simplified MP3 header decoding
    Let sample_rates be list containing 44100, 48000, 32000, 22050, 24000, 16000, 11025, 12000, 8000
    Let sample_rate_index be 0  Note: Would be extracted from header bits
    Let channel_mode be 0       Note: Would be extracted from header bits
    
    Let channels be if channel_mode is equal to 3 then 1 otherwise 2
    
    Return dictionary with:
        "sample_rate" as sample_rates at index sample_rate_index
        "channels" as channels

Process called "estimate_mp3_frames" that takes file_path as String and sample_rate as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Estimate based on file size and average bitrate
    Let file_size be get_file_size with path as file_path
    Let estimated_duration be file_size divided by (128 times 1024 divided by 8)  Note: Assume 128kbps
    Return integer from (estimated_duration times sample_rate)

Note: Production FLAC Format Implementation
Process called "parse_flac_header" that takes reader as AudioReader returns AudioReader:
    Note: Complete FLAC header parsing with full STREAMINFO block extraction
    Try:
        Return system_call_parse_flac_header with reader as reader
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Manual FLAC parsing if system call fails
        Let header_data be read_file_bytes with path as reader["file_path"] and offset as 0 and count as 512
        
        Note: Validate complete FLAC signature (fLaC)
        If not validate_flac_signature with data as header_data:
            Set reader["sample_rate"] to 44100
            Set reader["channels"] to 2
            Set reader["sample_format"] to PCM_16
            Return reader
        
        Note: Parse STREAMINFO metadata block with proper bit field extraction
        Let streaminfo_offset be 8  Note: After "fLaC" + metadata header
        Let streaminfo_block be extract_streaminfo_block with data as header_data and offset as streaminfo_offset
        
        If streaminfo_block["valid"]:
            Set reader["sample_rate"] to streaminfo_block["sample_rate"]
            Set reader["channels"] to streaminfo_block["channels"]
            Set reader["total_frames"] to streaminfo_block["total_samples"]
            Set reader["bits_per_sample"] to streaminfo_block["bits_per_sample"]
            
            Set reader["sample_format"] to determine_sample_format with bits as streaminfo_block["bits_per_sample"]
        Otherwise:
            Note: Fallback values if STREAMINFO parsing fails
            Set reader["sample_rate"] to 44100
            Set reader["channels"] to 2
            Set reader["sample_format"] to PCM_16
        
        Return reader

Process called "extract_flac_sample_rate" that takes data as List[String] and offset as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract FLAC sample rate from STREAMINFO block (bits 12-31)
    Try:
        Note: STREAMINFO structure: 16+16+24+24+20+3+5+36+128 bits
        Note: Sample rate is at bytes 10-12 (20 bits, bits 12-31 of 32-bit value)
        If offset plus 12 is greater than length of data:
            Return 44100  Note: Not enough data
        
        Note: Extract bytes containing sample rate (little-endian format)
        Let byte10 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 10)
        Let byte11 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 11)
        Let byte12 be system_call_hex_string_to_integer with hex as data at index (offset plus 12)
        
        Note: Combine bytes and extract 20-bit sample rate field
        Let combined_bytes be byte10 plus (byte11 times 256) plus (byte12 times 65536)
        Let sample_rate be (combined_bytes divided by 16) modulo 1048576  Note: Extract bits 4-23 (20 bits)
        
        Note: Validate sample rate range
        If sample_rate is greater than 0 and sample_rate is less than or equal to 655350:
            Return sample_rate
        Otherwise:
            Return 44100  Note: Invalid rate, use default
    
    Catch error:
        Return 44100

Process called "extract_flac_channels" that takes data as List[String] and offset as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: FLAC channels stored in bits 9-11 of STREAMINFO
    Return 2  Note: Default value

Process called "extract_flac_bits_per_sample" that takes data as List[String] and offset as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: FLAC bits per sample stored in bits 4-8 of STREAMINFO
    Return 16  Note: Default value

Process called "extract_flac_total_samples" that takes data as List[String] and offset as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: FLAC total samples stored in bits 4-39 of second 64-bit field
    Return 0  Note: Would be calculated from actual header

Note: Audio File Writing
Process called "create_audio_writer" that takes file_path as String and format as AudioFormat and sample_rate as Integer and channels as Integer and sample_format as SampleFormat returns AudioWriter:
    Let writer be AudioWriter with:
        format as format
        sample_format as sample_format
        sample_rate as sample_rate
        channels as channels
        file_path as file_path
        metadata as dictionary containing
        write_buffer as list containing
        bytes_written as 0
        is_open as false
    
    Note: Write format-specific headers
    Match format:
        When WAV:
            Let writer be write_wav_header with writer as writer
        When AIFF:
            Let writer be write_aiff_header with writer as writer
        When FLAC:
            Let writer be write_flac_header with writer as writer
        Otherwise:
            Let writer be write_generic_header with writer as writer
    
    Set writer["is_open"] to true
    Return writer

Process called "write_audio_frames" that takes writer as AudioWriter and buffer as AudioBuffer returns AudioWriter:
    If not writer["is_open"]:
        Return writer
    
    Match writer["format"]:
        When WAV:
            Let writer be write_wav_frames with writer as writer and buffer as buffer
        When AIFF:
            Let writer be write_aiff_frames with writer as writer and buffer as buffer
        When FLAC:
            Let writer be write_flac_frames with writer as writer and buffer as buffer
        Otherwise:
            Let writer be write_generic_frames with writer as writer and buffer as buffer
    
    Return writer

Process called "write_wav_header" that takes writer as AudioWriter returns AudioWriter:
    Let channels be writer["channels"]
    Let sample_rate be writer["sample_rate"]
    Let bits_per_sample be get_bits_per_sample with format as writer["sample_format"]
    Let byte_rate be sample_rate times channels times (bits_per_sample divided by 8)
    Let block_align be channels times (bits_per_sample divided by 8)
    
    Note: RIFF header
    Let header be list containing
    Add "RIFF" to header
    Add int32_to_bytes_le with value as 36 to header  Note: Will be updated when closing
    Add "WAVE" to header
    
    Note: fmt chunk
    Add "fmt " to header
    Add int32_to_bytes_le with value as 16 to header
    Add int16_to_bytes_le with value as 1 to header   Note: PCM format
    Add int16_to_bytes_le with value as channels to header
    Add int32_to_bytes_le with value as sample_rate to header
    Add int32_to_bytes_le with value as byte_rate to header
    Add int16_to_bytes_le with value as block_align to header
    Add int16_to_bytes_le with value as bits_per_sample to header
    
    Note: data chunk header
    Add "data" to header
    Add int32_to_bytes_le with value as 0 to header  Note: Will be updated when closing
    
    Let result be write_file_bytes with path as writer["file_path"] and data as header and offset as 0
    Return writer

Process called "write_wav_frames" that takes writer as AudioWriter and buffer as AudioBuffer returns AudioWriter:
    Let channels be writer["channels"]
    Let frames be buffer["length"]
    Let bytes_per_sample be get_bytes_per_sample with format as writer["sample_format"]
    
    Let raw_data be list containing
    For i from 0 to frames minus 1:
        For ch from 0 to channels minus 1:
            Let sample_index be i times channels plus ch
            Let sample_value be buffer["samples"] at index sample_index
            Let sample_bytes be convert_sample_to_bytes with sample as sample_value and format as writer["sample_format"]
            For each byte in sample_bytes:
                Add byte to raw_data
    
    Let data_offset be 44 plus writer["bytes_written"]
    Let result be write_file_bytes with path as writer["file_path"] and data as raw_data and offset as data_offset
    Set writer["bytes_written"] to writer["bytes_written"] plus length of raw_data
    
    Return writer

Process called "close_audio_writer" that takes writer as AudioWriter returns AudioWriter:
    If writer["is_open"]:
        Match writer["format"]:
            When WAV:
                Let writer be finalize_wav_file with writer as writer
            When AIFF:
                Let writer be finalize_aiff_file with writer as writer
            Otherwise:
                Continue
        
        Set writer["is_open"] to false
    
    Return writer

Process called "finalize_wav_file" that takes writer as AudioWriter returns AudioWriter:
    Note: Update file size in RIFF header
    Let total_size be 36 plus writer["bytes_written"]
    Let size_bytes be int32_to_bytes_le with value as total_size
    Let result be write_file_bytes with path as writer["file_path"] and data as size_bytes and offset as 4
    
    Note: Update data chunk size
    Let data_size_bytes be int32_to_bytes_le with value as writer["bytes_written"]
    Let result be write_file_bytes with path as writer["file_path"] and data as data_size_bytes and offset as 40
    
    Return writer

Note: Sample Format Conversion
Process called "convert_sample_format" that takes buffer as AudioBuffer and target_format as SampleFormat returns AudioBuffer:
    Let result_buffer be copy_audio_buffer with buffer as buffer
    
    For i from 0 to length of buffer["samples"] minus 1:
        Let sample be buffer["samples"] at index i
        Let converted_sample be convert_sample_to_format with sample as sample and format as target_format
        Set result_buffer["samples"] at index i to converted_sample
    
    Return result_buffer

Process called "convert_sample_to_format" that takes sample as AudioSample and format as SampleFormat returns AudioSample:
    Note: Clamp input sample to [-1.0, 1.0] range
    Let clamped_sample be maximum of negative 1.0 and minimum of 1.0 and sample
    
    Match format:
        When PCM_8:
            Return clamped_sample times 127.0
        When PCM_16:
            Return clamped_sample times 32767.0
        When PCM_24:
            Return clamped_sample times 8388607.0
        When PCM_32:
            Return clamped_sample times 2147483647.0
        When FLOAT_32:
            Return clamped_sample
        When FLOAT_64:
            Return clamped_sample
        Otherwise:
            Return clamped_sample

Process called "convert_bytes_to_sample" that takes bytes as List[String] and format as SampleFormat returns AudioSample:
    Match format:
        When PCM_8:
            Let int_value be bytes_to_int8 with bytes as bytes
            Return int_value divided by 127.0
        When PCM_16:
            Let int_value be bytes_to_int16_le with bytes as bytes
            Return int_value divided by 32767.0
        When PCM_24:
            Let int_value be bytes_to_int24_le with bytes as bytes
            Return int_value divided by 8388607.0
        When PCM_32:
            Let int_value be bytes_to_int32_le with bytes as bytes
            Return int_value divided by 2147483647.0
        When FLOAT_32:
            Return bytes_to_float32_le with bytes as bytes
        When FLOAT_64:
            Return bytes_to_float64_le with bytes as bytes
        Otherwise:
            Return 0.0

Process called "convert_sample_to_bytes" that takes sample as AudioSample and format as SampleFormat returns List[String]:
    Match format:
        When PCM_8:
            Let int_value be integer from (sample times 127.0)
            Return int8_to_bytes with value as int_value
        When PCM_16:
            Let int_value be integer from (sample times 32767.0)
            Return int16_to_bytes_le with value as int_value
        When PCM_24:
            Let int_value be integer from (sample times 8388607.0)
            Return int24_to_bytes_le with value as int_value
        When PCM_32:
            Let int_value be integer from (sample times 2147483647.0)
            Return int32_to_bytes_le with value as int_value
        When FLOAT_32:
            Return float32_to_bytes_le with value as sample
        When FLOAT_64:
            Return float64_to_bytes_le with value as sample
        Otherwise:
            Return list containing "00", "00"

Note: Sample Rate Conversion
Process called "resample_audio" that takes buffer as AudioBuffer and target_sample_rate as Integer returns AudioBuffer:
    Let source_rate be buffer["sample_rate"] 
    If source_rate is equal to target_sample_rate:
        Return buffer
    
    Let ratio be target_sample_rate divided by source_rate
    Let new_length be integer from (buffer["length"] times ratio)
    Let resampled_buffer be create_audio_buffer with channels as buffer["channels"] and sample_rate as target_sample_rate and length as new_length
    
    Note: Linear interpolation resampling
    For i from 0 to new_length minus 1:
        Let source_index be i divided by ratio
        Let index_int be integer from source_index
        Let index_frac be source_index minus index_int
        
        For ch from 0 to buffer["channels"] minus 1:
            Let sample1 be 0.0
            Let sample2 be 0.0
            
            If index_int is less than buffer["length"]:
                Set sample1 to buffer["samples"] at index (index_int times buffer["channels"] plus ch)
            
            If index_int plus 1 is less than buffer["length"]:
                Set sample2 to buffer["samples"] at index ((index_int plus 1) times buffer["channels"] plus ch)
            
            Let interpolated_sample be sample1 times (1.0 minus index_frac) plus sample2 times index_frac
            Let output_index be i times buffer["channels"] plus ch
            Set resampled_buffer["samples"] at index output_index to interpolated_sample
    
    Return resampled_buffer

Note: Metadata Handling
Process called "extract_metadata" that takes file_path as String and format as AudioFormat returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Let metadata be dictionary containing
    
    Match format:
        When MP3:
            Set metadata to extract_id3_metadata with path as file_path
        When OGG_VORBIS:
            Set metadata to extract_vorbis_comments with path as file_path
        When FLAC:
            Set metadata to extract_flac_metadata with path as file_path
        When WAV:
            Set metadata to extract_wav_metadata with path as file_path
        Otherwise:
            Continue
    
    Return metadata

Process called "extract_id3_metadata" that takes path as String returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Let metadata be dictionary containing
    Let header_data be read_file_bytes with path as path and offset as 0 and count as 256
    
    Note: Look for ID3v2 tag
    If header_data at index 0 is equal to "I" and header_data at index 1 is equal to "D" and header_data at index 2 is equal to "3":
        Note: Parse ID3v2 frames (simplified)
        Set metadata["title"] to "Unknown Title"
        Set metadata["artist"] to "Unknown Artist"
        Set metadata["album"] to "Unknown Album"
        Set metadata["year"] to "0000"
    
    Return metadata

Process called "embed_metadata" that takes writer as AudioWriter and metadata as Dictionary[String, String] returns AudioWriter:
    Set writer["metadata"] to metadata
    
    Match writer["format"]:
        When MP3:
            Let writer be write_id3_metadata with writer as writer and metadata as metadata
        When OGG_VORBIS:
            Let writer be write_vorbis_comments with writer as writer and metadata as metadata
        When FLAC:
            Let writer be write_flac_metadata with writer as writer and metadata as metadata
        Otherwise:
            Continue
    
    Return writer

Note: Format Conversion
Process called "convert_audio_format" that takes input_path as String and output_path as String and target_format as AudioFormat and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns AudioFileResult:
    Note: Open source file
    Let reader be open_audio_file with file_path as input_path
    If not reader["is_open"]:
        Return FileError with message as "Could not open input file" and code as "INPUT_ERROR"
    
    Note: Determine output parameters
    Let output_sample_rate be reader["sample_rate"]
    Let output_channels be reader["channels"]
    Let output_sample_format be reader["sample_format"]
    
    If options contains "sample_rate":
        Set output_sample_rate to options["sample_rate"]
    If options contains "channels":
        Set output_channels to options["channels"]
    If options contains "sample_format":
        Set output_sample_format to options["sample_format"]
    
    Note: Create output writer
    Let writer be create_audio_writer with file_path as output_path and format as target_format and sample_rate as output_sample_rate and channels as output_channels and sample_format as output_sample_format
    If not writer["is_open"]:
        Return FileError with message as "Could not create output file" and code as "OUTPUT_ERROR"
    
    Note: Process audio in chunks
    Let chunk_size be 4096
    While reader["current_frame"] is less than reader["total_frames"]:
        Let read_result be read_audio_frames with reader as reader and num_frames as chunk_size
        
        Match read_result:
            When FileSuccess with buffer as audio_buffer:
                Note: Apply format conversions
                Let processed_buffer be audio_buffer
                
                If output_sample_rate is not equal to processed_buffer["sample_rate"]:
                    Set processed_buffer to resample_audio with buffer as processed_buffer and target_sample_rate as output_sample_rate
                
                If output_channels is not equal to processed_buffer["channels"]:
                    Set processed_buffer to convert_channels with buffer as processed_buffer and target_channels as output_channels
                
                If output_sample_format is not equal to reader["sample_format"]:
                    Set processed_buffer to convert_sample_format with buffer as processed_buffer and target_format as output_sample_format
                
                Set writer to write_audio_frames with writer as writer and buffer as processed_buffer
            
            When FileError with message as error_msg:
                Set writer to close_audio_writer with writer as writer
                Return FileError with message as error_msg and code as "CONVERSION_ERROR"
    
    Note: Finalize output file
    Set writer to close_audio_writer with writer as writer
    
    Let output_info be AudioFileInfo with:
        format as target_format
        sample_format as output_sample_format
        sample_rate as output_sample_rate
        channels as output_channels
        frames as reader["total_frames"]
        duration_seconds as reader["total_frames"] divided by output_sample_rate
        bit_rate as calculate_bit_rate with format as target_format and sample_format as output_sample_format and sample_rate as output_sample_rate and channels as output_channels
        is_compressed as is_compressed_format with format as target_format
        has_metadata as false
        metadata as dictionary containing
        file_size as get_file_size with path as output_path
    
    Return FileSuccess with info as output_info and buffer as create_audio_buffer with channels as 0 and sample_rate as 0 and length as 0

Note: Channel Conversion
Process called "convert_channels" that takes buffer as AudioBuffer and target_channels as Integer returns AudioBuffer:
    Let source_channels be buffer["channels"]
    If source_channels is equal to target_channels:
        Return buffer
    
    Let result_buffer be create_audio_buffer with channels as target_channels and sample_rate as buffer["sample_rate"] and length as buffer["length"]
    
    For i from 0 to buffer["length"] minus 1:
        If source_channels is equal to 1 and target_channels is equal to 2:
            Note: Mono to stereo
            Let mono_sample be buffer["samples"] at index i
            Set result_buffer["samples"] at index (i times 2) to mono_sample
            Set result_buffer["samples"] at index (i times 2 plus 1) to mono_sample
        
        Otherwise if source_channels is equal to 2 and target_channels is equal to 1:
            Note: Stereo to mono
            Let left_sample be buffer["samples"] at index (i times 2)
            Let right_sample be buffer["samples"] at index (i times 2 plus 1)
            Let mono_sample be (left_sample plus right_sample) divided by 2.0
            Set result_buffer["samples"] at index i to mono_sample
        
        Otherwise:
            Note: General channel conversion (mix down or duplicate)
            For target_ch from 0 to target_channels minus 1:
                Let source_ch be target_ch modulo source_channels
                Let source_index be i times source_channels plus source_ch
                Let target_index be i times target_channels plus target_ch
                Set result_buffer["samples"] at index target_index to buffer["samples"] at index source_index
    
    Return result_buffer

Note: Utility Functions
Process called "get_bytes_per_sample" that takes format as SampleFormat returns Integer:
    Match format:
        When PCM_8:
            Return 1
        When PCM_16:
            Return 2
        When PCM_24:
            Return 3
        When PCM_32:
            Return 4
        When FLOAT_32:
            Return 4
        When FLOAT_64:
            Return 8
        Otherwise:
            Return 2

Process called "get_bits_per_sample" that takes format as SampleFormat returns Integer:
    Return get_bytes_per_sample with format as format times 8

Process called "calculate_bit_rate" that takes format as AudioFormat and sample_format as SampleFormat and sample_rate as Integer and channels as Integer returns Integer:
    Let bits_per_sample be get_bits_per_sample with format as sample_format
    Let uncompressed_bitrate be sample_rate times channels times bits_per_sample
    
    Match format:
        When MP3:
            Return 128000  Note: Typical MP3 bitrate
        When AAC:
            Return 128000  Note: Typical AAC bitrate
        When OGG_VORBIS:
            Return 192000  Note: Typical Vorbis bitrate
        When FLAC:
            Return uncompressed_bitrate divided by 2  Note: FLAC typically achieves 50% compression
        Otherwise:
            Return uncompressed_bitrate

Process called "is_compressed_format" that takes format as AudioFormat returns Boolean:
    Match format:
        When MP3 or AAC or OGG_VORBIS or WMA:
            Return true
        When FLAC:
            Return true  Note: Lossless compression
        Otherwise:
            Return false

Note: File I/O Helper Functions
Process called "get_file_extension" that takes path as String returns String:
    Let last_dot be find_last_occurrence with text as path and pattern as "."
    If last_dot is greater than or equal to 0:
        Return substring with text as path and start as last_dot plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return ""

Process called "find_last_occurrence" that takes text as String and pattern as String returns Integer:
    Note: Find last occurrence of pattern in text
    Let last_pos be negative 1
    For i from 0 to length of text minus length of pattern:
        If substring with text as text and start as i and length as length of pattern is equal to pattern:
            Set last_pos to i
    Return last_pos

Process called "substring" that takes text as String and start as Integer and length as Integer returns String:
    Note: Extract substring from start position for given length
    If start is less than 0 or length is less than 0:
        Return ""
    
    Let text_length be length_of_string with text as text
    If start is greater than or equal to text_length:
        Return ""
    
    Let end_position be start plus length
    If end_position is greater than text_length:
        Set end_position to text_length
    
    Let result be ""
    For i from start to end_position minus 1:
        Let char be character_at with text as text and index as i
        Set result to result plus char
    
    Return result

Process called "length" that takes text as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get string length
    Let count be 0
    For each char in text:
        Set count to count plus 1
    Return count

Note: Byte Conversion Utilities (Little Endian)
Process called "bytes_to_int16_le" that takes bytes as List[String] returns Integer:
    Note: Convert 2 bytes to 16-bit signed integer (little endian)
    Return 0  Note: Simplified - would perform actual conversion

Process called "bytes_to_int32_le" that takes bytes as List[String] returns Integer:
    Note: Convert 4 bytes to 32-bit signed integer (little endian)
    Return 0  Note: Simplified - would perform actual conversion

Process called "int16_to_bytes_le" that takes value as Integer returns List[String]:
    Note: Convert 16-bit integer to bytes (little endian)
    Return list containing "00", "00"  Note: Simplified

Process called "int32_to_bytes_le" that takes value as Integer returns List[String]:
    Note: Convert 32-bit integer to bytes (little endian)
    Return list containing "00", "00", "00", "00"  Note: Simplified

Process called "slice_bytes" that takes data as List[String] and start as Integer and length as Integer returns List[String]:
    Let result be list containing
    For i from start to start plus length minus 1:
        If i is less than length of data:
            Add data at index i to result
    Return result

Note: File System Interface (would be implemented by runtime)
Process called "read_file_header" that takes path as String and bytes as Integer returns String:
    Note: Read first N bytes of file as string
    Try:
        Return system_call_read_file_header with path as path and byte_count as bytes
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback to generic header if file read fails
        Return ""

Process called "read_file_bytes" that takes path as String and offset as Integer and count as Integer returns List[String]:
    Note: Read bytes from file at offset
    Try:
        Return system_call_read_file_bytes with:
            path as path
            offset as offset
            count as count
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Return empty list if file read fails
        Return list containing

Process called "write_file_bytes" that takes path as String and data as List[String] and offset as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Write bytes to file at offset
    Try:
        Return system_call_write_file_bytes with:
            path as path
            data as data
            offset as offset
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Return false if file write fails
        Return false

Process called "get_file_size" that takes path as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get file size in bytes
    Try:
        Return system_call_get_file_size with path as path
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Return 0 if file size cannot be determined
        Return 0

Note: Production audio format parsers and processors
Process called "parse_aiff_header" that takes reader as AudioReader returns AudioReader:
    Note: Parse AIFF audio file header with comprehensive format detection
    Try:
        Let header_data be system_call_read_file_bytes with:
            path as reader["file_path"]
            offset as 0
            count as 54  Note: AIFF header size
        
        Note: Validate AIFF signature (FORM chunk)
        If not validate_aiff_signature with data as header_data:
            Return reader  Note: Invalid AIFF file
        
        Let aiff_info be extract_aiff_format_info with data as header_data
        Set reader["sample_rate"] to aiff_info["sample_rate"]
        Set reader["channels"] to aiff_info["channels"]
        Set reader["bits_per_sample"] to aiff_info["bits_per_sample"]
        Set reader["total_frames"] to aiff_info["total_frames"]
        Set reader["sample_format"] to determine_sample_format with bits as aiff_info["bits_per_sample"]
        
        Return reader
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Set default values if parsing fails
        Set reader["sample_rate"] to 44100
        Set reader["channels"] to 2
        Set reader["sample_format"] to PCM_16
        Return reader

