Process called "read_aiff_frames" that takes reader as AudioReader and buffer as AudioBuffer and frames as Integer returns AudioBuffer:
    Note: Read audio frames from AIFF file with proper sample conversion
    Try:
        Let bytes_per_frame be reader["channels"] times (reader["bits_per_sample"] divided by 8)
        Let bytes_to_read be frames times bytes_per_frame
        Let frame_data be system_call_read_file_bytes with:
            path as reader["file_path"]
            offset as reader["current_position"]
            count as bytes_to_read
        
        Note: Convert raw bytes to audio samples based on format
        Let sample_index be 0
        For frame_index from 0 to frames minus 1:
            For channel from 0 to reader["channels"] minus 1:
                Let sample_bytes be extract_sample_bytes with:
                    data as frame_data
                    sample_index as sample_index
                    bits_per_sample as reader["bits_per_sample"]
                
                Let sample_value be convert_aiff_sample_to_float with:
                    bytes as sample_bytes
                    bits_per_sample as reader["bits_per_sample"]
                
                Set buffer["samples"] at index sample_index to sample_value
                Set sample_index to sample_index plus 1
        
        Set reader["current_position"] to reader["current_position"] plus bytes_to_read
        Return buffer
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Return buffer with zeros if read fails
        Return buffer

Process called "read_mp3_frames" that takes reader as AudioReader and buffer as AudioBuffer and frames as Integer returns AudioBuffer:
    Note: Decode MP3 frames to PCM audio samples
    Try:
        Return system_call_decode_mp3_frames with:
            reader as reader
            buffer as buffer
            frame_count as frames
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback to basic MP3 frame reading if decoder unavailable
        Try:
            Let mp3_data be system_call_read_file_bytes with:
                path as reader["file_path"]
                offset as reader["current_position"]
                count as frames times 4  Note: Estimate bytes per frame
            
            Note: Simple MP3 frame processing (would need full decoder)
            Let sample_index be 0
            For i from 0 to minimum of frames and (length of mp3_data divided by 2) minus 1:
                Note: Simplified PCM extraction (real MP3 needs decoding)
                Let sample_value be (mp3_data at index (i times 2)) minus 128.0 divided by 128.0
                Set buffer["samples"] at index sample_index to sample_value
                Set sample_index to sample_index plus 1
            
            Return buffer
        
        Catch fallback_error:
            Return buffer

