Process called "write_aiff_header" that takes writer as AudioWriter returns AudioWriter:
    Note: Write AIFF file header with proper chunk structure
    Try:
        Note: Calculate file sizes
        Let samples_per_channel be writer["total_frames"]
        Let bytes_per_sample be writer["bits_per_sample"] divided by 8
        Let sound_data_size be samples_per_channel times writer["channels"] times bytes_per_sample
        Let comm_chunk_size be 18
        Let ssnd_chunk_size be sound_data_size plus 8
        Let form_size be 4 plus 8 plus comm_chunk_size plus 8 plus ssnd_chunk_size
        
        Note: Build AIFF header
        Let header_bytes be list containing
        
        Note: FORM chunk
        Add "FORM" to header_bytes
        Add int32_to_bytes_be with value as form_size to header_bytes
        Add "AIFF" to header_bytes
        
        Note: COMM chunk
        Add "COMM" to header_bytes
        Add int32_to_bytes_be with value as comm_chunk_size to header_bytes
        Add int16_to_bytes_be with value as writer["channels"] to header_bytes
        Add int32_to_bytes_be with value as samples_per_channel to header_bytes
        Add int16_to_bytes_be with value as writer["bits_per_sample"] to header_bytes
        Add ieee_extended_80bit_from_sample_rate with rate as writer["sample_rate"] to header_bytes
        
        Note: SSND chunk header
        Add "SSND" to header_bytes
        Add int32_to_bytes_be with value as ssnd_chunk_size to header_bytes
        Add int32_to_bytes_be with value as 0 to header_bytes  Note: Offset
        Add int32_to_bytes_be with value as 0 to header_bytes  Note: Block size
        
        Let success be system_call_write_file_bytes with:
            path as writer["file_path"]
            data as header_bytes
            offset as 0
        
        If success:
            Set writer["header_written"] to true
        
        Return writer
    
    Catch error:
        Return writer

