Process called "float32_to_bytes_le" that takes value as Float returns List[String]:
    Note: Convert 32-bit float to 4 bytes (little-endian IEEE 754)
    Try:
        Return system_call_ieee754_float_to_bytes with:
            value as value
            endianness as "little"
            precision as 32
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Manual IEEE 754 conversion if system call fails
        Note: Handle special cases
        If value is equal to 0.0:
            Return list containing "00", "00", "00", "00"
        
        Let sign_bit be 0
        Let working_value be value
        If working_value is less than 0.0:
            Set sign_bit to 1
            Set working_value to negative working_value
        
        Note: Simplified IEEE 754 encoding
        Let exponent be 127  Note: Bias
        Let mantissa_bits be integer from (working_value times 8388608.0) modulo 8388608
        
        Note: Pack into 32-bit integer
        Let bits be (sign_bit times 2147483648) plus (exponent times 8388608) plus mantissa_bits
        
        Note: Extract bytes in little-endian order
        Let byte0 be bits modulo 256
        Let byte1 be (bits divided by 256) modulo 256
        Let byte2 be (bits divided by 65536) modulo 256
        Let byte3 be (bits divided by 16777216) modulo 256
        
        Return list containing:
            integer_to_hex_manual with value as byte0
            integer_to_hex_manual with value as byte1
            integer_to_hex_manual with value as byte2
            integer_to_hex_manual with value as byte3

